    "action_input": "Newton's First Law of Motion, also known as the Law of Inertia, states that an object at rest will stay at rest, and an object in motion will stay in motion with the same speed and in the same direction unless acted upon by an unbalanced external force. Essentially, this law means that if there's no net force acting on an object (if all the external forces cancel each other out), then the object will maintain a constant velocity. If that velocity is zero, the object remains at rest. If an external force is applied, the state of motion of the object is changed, which could mean the object starts moving from a rest position, changes its velocity, or changes its direction."
}
